---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="FOSS 4 Security Manifesto">
  <main class="manifesto-container">
    <header>
      <h1>Securing the Digital World, Together. Openly.</h1>
    </header>
    
    <section class="principle">
      <h2>1. True Open Source, No Compromises</h2>
      <p>We believe cybersecurity must be built on trust, and trust begins with transparency.
      All projects under the FOSS 4 Security umbrella are genuinely open source:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Freely accessible source code</li>
        <li>FOSS licenses</li>
        <li>Transparent development and governance</li>
      </ul>
      <p>No traps, no hidden strings. Just clean, auditable, modifiable code.</p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="principle">
      <h2>2. Free Community Editions for All</h2>
      <p>Security is a fundamental right, not a luxury.
      That's why all FOSS 4 Security tools provide fully functional community editions — without essential features gating, time bombs, or paywalls.</p>
      <p>You can test, learn, and secure — without needing a credit card or approval from procurement.</p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="principle">
      <h2>3. A Cohesive Ecosystem, Not a Logo Farm</h2>
      <p>We don't do "just a list."</p>
      <p>FOSS 4 Security tools are designed to work together — through shared APIs, integration standards, or bridges — making it easy to combine threat detection, risk analysis, workload protection, policy enforcement, compliance automation, and more.</p>
      <p>Our goal: a modular, interoperable cybersecurity stack, where tools collaborate instead of coexist.</p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="principle">
      <h2>4. Driven by Community, Guided by Purpose</h2>
      <p>We are builders, defenders, and tinkerers — united by a mission to make digital life safer for all.</p>
      <p>Our community shares not just code, but knowledge, ideas, and responsibility.</p>
      <p>From solo devs to global teams, everyone has a voice in shaping the future of open security.</p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="principle">
      <h2>5. Open Security as a business enabler</h2>
      <p>In a time of increasing digital threats, silos and secrets don't help.</p>
      <p>We believe in collaborative defense, where transparency, community, and openness are our strongest shields.</p>
      <p>Once you are ready, you can support the initiative by considering the paid/pro plan of the solutions.</p>
    </section>
    
    <footer>
      <p class="call-to-action">Join us. Contribute. Fork. Fix. Share.</p>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .manifesto-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #333;
  }
  
  header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #eaeaea;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  h1 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    color: #2a5caa;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  .principle {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #2a5caa;
    border-left: 4px solid #2a5caa;
    padding-left: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  ul {
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  footer {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px solid #eaeaea;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .call-to-action {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #2a5caa;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .manifesto-container {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    h1 {
      font-size: 1.8rem;
    }
    
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
    }
    
    .call-to-action {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
